description: Number of nonisomorphic connected binary n-state automata without output under input permutations.
references: M. A. Harrison, A census of finite automata, Canad. J. Math., 17, No. 1, 1965, p. 110.
F. Harary and E. Palmer, Graphical Enumeration, 1973.
example: There are 40000 nonisomorphic connected binary 5-state automata under input permutations.
author: _Vladeta Jovovic_, Apr 22 2000
